    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-03T17:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-03T17:26:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8353: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d240fn1">Drafted by <persName>Paul W. Jones</persName> and
                        signed by Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1"
                            >Murphy</persName>. Repeated for information to Wellington and <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-03T18:26:00-04:00"
                            >August 3, 1953—6:26 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. Take up following <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> election matters most
                    urgently with <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss>: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Re Eighth <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Presidency inform <gloss
                                target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> in strict confidence US has decided
                            support <persName corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1">Madam Pandit</persName> if she
                            becomes candidate but will not campaign on her behalf, and request
                                <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> transmit to <persName
                                corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1">Madam Pandit</persName> personal message
                            from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName>
                            included in immediately following telegram. Also ascertain from <gloss
                                target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> whether she is definitely a candidate.
                            Ind Emb recently raised this matter with Department.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Re <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> election inform <gloss
                                target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> US has given careful consideration
                            candidacies of New Zealand and India to replace Pakistan and has decided
                            support New Zealand. As <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> aware, we
                            have in past taken views Commonwealth Members into acount in determining
                            our position this seat, and we understand New Zealand has support most
                            Commonwealth Members. We appreciate problem raised <gloss
                                target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> aide-mémoire regarding desirability
                            adequate Asian representation in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> and
                            will continue give thought this problem.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>In accordance Department’s discussions New Zealand Embassy inform New Zealand
                    Prime Minister as soon as you have given Indians info on <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> position and in case any delay consult with him re timing your
                    approach Indians. <persName>Holland</persName> intends discuss <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> seat with <persName corresp="#p_NEHRURK1"
                        >Nehru</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
